overlaps are obtained with \code{\link[TPD:TPDs]{TPD::TPDs()}} and \code{\link[TPD:dissim]{TPD::dissim()}}; the returned
matrix is \code{TPD::dissim()}'s population-level dissimilarity, and its
decomposition into the shared and non-shared (turnover-like) components is
returned alongside when available.

The resulting dissimilarity is a drop-in, ITV-aware replacement for a
species-mean distance matrix: it can be ordinated (\code{cmdscale(as.dist(d))}),
clustered, or fed to a distance-based diversity index (e.g. Rao's quadratic
entropy via \code{\link[TPD:Rao]{TPD::Rao()}}, or a functional Hill number).
